==English==
[[Image:Mango 24.jpg|thumb|mangoes (fruit)]]
===Etymology===
Portuguese [[manga]], from Tamil[[മാങ്ങ]].

Mango is derived from Tamil word "Maanga".
Maanga is the unripe mango.
Maa + Gaa = Mango + unripe fruit

[[Malayalam]] is youngest of the [[dravidian]] languagues, which is about 1000 years old. [[Tamil]] is the first [[dravidian]] language. Please look into [[tamil]] [[sangam]] literature to find references to [[maa]].


The word mango is from the Malayalam (the language of [[Kerala]], [[India]]) word മാങ്ങ /ˈmäːŋːə/. Portuguese explorers tasted mangoes for the first time in Kerala, and borrowed the word into their language, rendering it as 'manga', which was in turn borrowed into English.

